[center][size=6][b]marth Resurgence Overhaul[/b][/size]
[i]late-game progression past the cap — the ceiling is where it begins[/i][/center]
[line]

A load-order mod that rebalances late-game power scaling, currently built for [b]Requiem[/b]-based lists (developed against LoreRim, Skyrim SE 1.6.1170). Early and mid game are untouched — every feature gates on endgame investment, so you and your followers keep ascending while enemies keep their lethality. Where progression normally flatlines is where it surges back.

Built entirely on Linux with no Creation Kit and no xEdit: the plugin is generated byte-by-byte from Python, and the SKSE plugin builds on GitHub Actions.

[size=5][b]Features[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Elemental absorb[/b] — resistances scale past 100%; above 100%, that element's incoming damage heals you instead (full absorb at a configurable resistance). Computed per hit by the SKSE plugin from the real post-skill/perk magnitude.
[*][b]Physical DR past the armor cap[/b] — damage reduction keeps scaling beyond the engine's cap, gated and ceilinged by your armor mastery. 99% DR demands best-in-list gear [i]and[/i] full mastery. Only EARNED armor counts past the cap: wards and flesh spells protect fully up to the engine cap but cannot push beyond it.
[*][b]14-skill Mastery system[/b] (via Custom Skills Framework) — each skill unlocks at base 100 and trains through real use on a steeply rising cost curve. Weapon and armor XP are credited per hit, damage-scaled and normalized to your own typical blow; magic trains by magicka actually spent. Level-ups show the real vanilla skill-up banner, chime and all.
[*][b]Magic capstones[/b] — at mastery 50, a school's master (two-handed) spells become castable one-handed; at mastery 100 they become dual-cast eligible (the school's dual-cast perk is still required — dual-casting a master spell is an earned achievement).
[*][b]Honest status[/b] — the magic menu's Active Effects page shows your real damage reduction and strongest-element absorb, live; the MCM adds a Progress page for all 14 masteries, feature toggles, tuning sliders, and a full Live Status panel.
[*][b]Zero script tax[/b] — all combat and cast detection is native and player-filtered. No polling, no global Papyrus listeners, no heartbeat.
[/list]

[size=5][b]FAQ[/b][/size]

[b]Doesn't this ruin Requiem's balance?[/b]
It changes nothing about enemies — stats, encounter design, and lethality are intact. Every feature sits [i]past[/i] the point where a character has already hit the skill, armor, and resistance ceilings and stopped progressing. It extends the top of the curve; it doesn't reshape the rest of it.

[b]Isn't it too easy to become overpowered?[/b]
Getting there is a long, earned road. A mastery only [i]begins[/i] at base skill 100, then costs progressively more per level on a steep endgame curve. Weapon XP only counts hits on living, hostile targets, normalized to your own typical blow — weak-mob farming earns no faster than real fighting. I doubt most people will even get close at recommended settings.

[b]Can I turn it down, or off?[/b]
Yes. Every feature toggles independently in the MCM, and the numbers are sliders. If a feature isn't to your taste, switch it off; if only the pacing is, tune it.

[size=5][b]Install[/b][/size]
One flat package — no FOMOD, every choice is a runtime MCM toggle. The optional file rebalances the Experience mod's ini (only take it if you run Experience). Upgrading from any 0.x: overwrite and play; migrations run in place.

[size=5][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
SKSE64, Address Library for SKSE Plugins, SkyUI 5.2+, Custom Skills Framework, and powerofthree's Papyrus Extender. The bundled MRO.dll is part of the mod and required.

[size=5][b]Notes[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Contains only original work; redistributes no assets from Requiem or any other mod.
[*]Source, docs, and full changelog: github.com/marthofdoom/MRO
[/list]
